  <summary date="2025-03-14T20:25:08Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Standing Against Houthi Aggression Act

This bill requires (1) the Department of State to designate Ansarallah, the&#160;Iran-backed movement in Yemen also known as the Houthis, as a foreign terrorist organization; and (2) the President to impose property- and visa-blocking sanctions with respect to Ansarallah and any foreign person who is a member, agent, or affiliate of, or owned or controlled by, Ansarallah.</summary>
